### Required vs Optional Variables
- **Required**: API keys, database URLs, critical configuration
- **Optional**: Debug flags, optional integrations, feature toggles

## Client Configuration

### Cursor IDE Configuration
Add to `~/.cursor/mcp.json`:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "your-server-name": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/absolute/path/to/your-server/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "YOUR_API_KEY": "your-actual-api-key-here"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Alternative: Using pnpm (auto-loads .env)
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "your-server-name": {
      "command": "pnpm",
      "args": ["start"],
      "cwd": "/absolute/path/to/your-server"
    }
  }
}
```

## Configuration Validation
- Validate required environment variables on server startup
- Provide clear error messages for missing configuration
- Use fallback values for non-critical settings
- Document all environment variables in [.env.example](mdc:.env.example)
